CAREY BELL

Carey Bell, who has worked with Muddy Waters, Willie Dixon, John Lee Hooker and
Earl Hooker, is one of Chicago's outstanding harmonica players. Carey demonstrates his
classic, unadulterated style that recalls his mentors, Walter Horton and Little Walter Jacobs.
The Detroit News said Bell "plays a tough yet essentially mellow style of blues, a bracing mix
of deep country roots and just enough citified grit to penetrate a noisy, musky, gin-soaked bar.


Enjoy your copy of MusicMatch Jukebox!

THAT SPOT RIGHT THERE  (14 second demo clip)

Do the twist thing ....... in that spot right there.
Do the twist thing ........in that spot right there. 
I don't care, long as you do it in that spot there. 
First in the morning, first at night, 
Come on over here darlin', let me hold you tight.
In that spot right there, in that spot right there. 
I wanna hold you, in that spot right there. 

Yeah, do the twist thing, do the twist thing on me.
Oh mama, do the twist thing now, do the twist just for me. 
You made me love you, in that spot right there. 

Do the quick thing, do the twist right now. 
Do the twist Babe, do the twist right now. 
Come on babe, in this old house, I want you to do the twist right now. 
In that spot, over here in that spot. Oh Lord, Lord.
